properties.text: Heaven's Point stands tall above Castle Moss.
Castle Moss' Moss-Knights stand alone against the armies of Heaven.
No one knows what lies within the bowels of the Penitent Tower, as only the angelic warriors of Heaven's Point are allowed within.
Keep an eye out for CASTLE SIGILS, like the Sigil of CASTLE BARON. They may unravel the mysteries of Castle Moss.
BEWARE: Undead. Be sure to HOLD SPACEBAR to hold your weapon in front of you!

There are treasure chests littered around, and inside Castle Moss. Within the chests you'll find items to help you on your adventure, such as the Red Hearts of Dissodia, which have restorative properties.

There are pressure plates that, when pressed in the right sequence, will unlock a door. If you press them in the wrong sequence? You don't want to press them in the wrong sequence. Each pressure plate represents one of the three Kingdoms of Dissodia: Castle Baron, Heaven's Point, and Castle Moss.
